          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-56 lnet: SMP improvements for LNet",
        "message": "LU-56 lnet: SMP improvements for LNet\n\nThis patch contains:\n- fine-grained locking for LNet, LNET_LOCK is replaced by two percpt\n  locks: lnet_net_lock(i) and lnet_res_lock(i)\n- LNet has multiple processing partitions, EQ callbacks can happen\n  concurrently now.\n- LNetMEAttach can new @pos = LNET_INS_LOCAL, which means ME and MD\n  will be attached on local partition of current CPU.\n- many code changes to support no-global-lock LNet.\n- there are a few issues in this patch, they will be fixed very soon.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ia6ff45606009f430d27d3bbe693b49d485570c1b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
